David A. Ishay | Founder of The Ishay Group


David A. Ishay, founder of The Ishay Group, a Brooklyn NY native since 1972, has founded, owned and operated businesses ranging from manufacturing, retail, marketing and sales, advertising, publishing, mail order, e-commerce, (all under the brands of American Spirit, You Sport, and YRB). All the while, Mr. Ishay has invested in Real Estate. In the process, he has briefly operated a French Bistro (La Barrique), ostensibly to improve the tenant positioning of the Bryant Park office building. Presently, Mr. Ishay is solely committed to managing and developing properties.
Mr. Ishay has owned and managed THE MODERN ARTS building, a NYC office building (38 West 39 St., Bryant Park area) since 1999, and is currently planning an extension and addition to the property to optimize and tap into its air rights potential. Currently, David Ishay is involved in multiple development projects ranging from ground up construction, conversion, rehab, extensions and additions on multiple properties simultaneously. The following projects are all expected to be completed in 2019:

Manhattan – Bryant Park: office building (extension and addition)
Brooklyn – PLS, (Prospect Lefferts South): 67 apartment units (ground up construction)
Jersey City – The Heights: 14 apartments and retail (conversion)
Newark: 216 apartments (rehab)

A full bio on David A. Ishay can be seen at: www.linkedin.com/pub/david-ishay/9/334/a44






A heritage of vision, passion, and diligence 

















FIMI Opportunity Funds - Ishay Davidi































































































				Ishay Davidi			



Founder and Chief Executive Officer
Mr. Davidi is the Founder and has served as Chief Executive Officer of FIMI Opportunity Funds since 1996. Prior to establishing FIMI, Mr. Davidi was the CEO of the Tikvah Fund, a private Israeli investment fund founded by the late Sanford Bernstein. Mr. Davidi also held senior management positions in a variety of leading Israeli industrial and high-tech companies. Mr. Davidi is the Chairman of the Board of Directors of Inrom Construction Industries (TASE), Hadera Paper (TASE) and Polyram Plastic Industries. He is a Director of Gilat Satellite Networks (NASDAQ/TASE), Ham-Let (TASE), Bet Shemesh Engines (TASE), Overseas Commerce, C.Mer Industries (TASE), Novolog (Pharm-Up 1966), Inrom Industries and Rekah Pharmaceutical Industries (TASE). 
































